ADMA_list_directory_contents.description: Given a path of directory on ADMA, return the list of paths under the directory.

ADMA_list_directory_contents&dir_path.description: ADMA_list_directory_contents&dir_path is a path of the directory on the ADMA system. The format should be like path/to/directory, with 0 or more / in the path.

ADMA_list_directory_contents&output_list.description: ADMA_list_directory_contents&output_list is a list of paths in the ADMA system.
ADMA_list_directory_contents&output_list_current_index is the current index of ADMA_list_directory_contents&output_list.

iter_list_1.call_condition: Do not call this method if ADMA_list_directory_contents&output_list_current_index is greater than the length of ADMA_list_directory_contents&output_list
iter_list_1.description: Given a list of path and an index, return the path at the index and increase the index by 1.

iter_list_2.call_condition: Do not call this method if ADMA_list_directory_contents&output_list_current_index is greater than the length of ADMA_list_directory_contents&output_list
iter_list_2.description: Given a list of path and an index, return the path at the index and increase the index by 1.

ADMA_get_meta_data.description: Given a path on ADMA, return the meta data of the path on the ADMA server.

ADMA_get_meta_data&path.description: ADMA_get_meta_data&path is a path of the file or folder on the ADMA server.

ADMA_get_meta_data&meta_data.description: ADMA_get_meta_data&meta_data is the meta data of the file or folder on the ADMA server.

ADMA_push_to_meta_data_list.description: Given a meta data, push the meta data to the list.

ADMA_push_to_meta_data_list&output_list.description: ADMA_push_to_meta_data_list&output_list is a list of meta data of the file or folder on the ADMA server.

ADMA_menu_option.description: Given a menu name and a path, return the url of the menu on the ADMA server.

ADMA_menu_option&menu_name.description: ADMA_menu_option&menu_name is the name of the menu on the ADMA server. It should be one of the following: search, share_with_me, files, data, models, tools, collections, documentation, api.

ADMA_menu_option&path.description: ADMA_menu_option&path is the path of the menu on the ADMA server. It should be in the format of path/to/directory, with 0 or more / in the path.

ADMA_menu_option&menu_url.description: ADMA_menu_option&menu_url is the url of the menu on the ADMA server.

JD_ENREEC_boundary_in_field.description: Given a field_id, return the boundary of the field.

JD_ENREEC_boundary_in_field&field_id.description: JD_ENREEC_boundary_in_field&field_id is the id of the field in ENREEC.

JD_ENREEC_boundary_in_field&boundary.description: JD_ENREEC_boundary_in_field&boundary is the boundary of the field in ENREEC.
